SMEs trading cross-border face 11% higher compliance costs compared to those trading only domestically. We propose to extend VAT exemption so that SMEs established in another Member States benefit from VAT exemption where they do business → https://t.co/Hi41yJcJPV #FairTaxation https://t.co/5z7hGqYoeE

In addition to standard VAT rate of minimum 15%, we are giving Member States more autonomy on rates:
📌two separate reduced rates of between 5% and the standard rate 
📌one 'zero rate'
📌one reduced rate set at between 0% and the reduced rates. 
More → https://t.co/Hi41yJcJPV https://t.co/mYEcJe0fnU

data.text: We also want to restrict the use of microplastics intentionally added in cosmetics so that they don't end up in the sea and eventually in our food. #PlasticsStrategy https://t.co/1uTEZ4d8uz

Bottles, bags or cups: single-use plastics represent half of the items found on EU beaches but can take 500 years to breakdown into smaller pieces. Later this year, we will come forward with a proposal on single-use plastics #PlasticsStrategy https://t.co/7WtxiYy3i0

Better product design makes plastics recycling easier. We will consider new product requirements under our Ecodesign Directive to include recyclability requirements #PlasticsStrategy https://t.co/2cO1D7tXd5
Waste generated on ships should be delivered on land. We are putting forward a legislative proposal on port reception facilities to prevent littering at sea. #PlasticsStrategy https://t.co/Fp3dinS0mY
Our #PlasticsStrategy focuses on 4 priority areas to transform the way products are designed, produced, used and recycled in the EU towards a more circular economy. https://t.co/siiIZogEJ2

Global production of plastics has increased twentyfold since the 1960s. Every year, Europeans generate 25 million tonnes of plastic waste, of which, less than 30% is collected for recycling. We cannot go on like this. #PlasticsStrategy https://t.co/LFi7co7NZV

Today, we unveil our first-ever European #PlasticsStrategy with great ambitions in mind: reduce single-use plastics, restrict microplastics and ensure that all plastics packaging placed on EU market are recyclable by 2030. Thread. https://t.co/TbuKdVALB8 https://t.co/RkyPbA1fmf

"If we don't change the way we produce and use plastics, there will be more plastics than fish in our oceans by 2050" say vice-Presidents @TimmermansEU and @jyrkikatainen during the presentation of the new EU #PlasticsStrategy https://t.co/0NtpCSEDVZ
